Lemany  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Szczytno, within Szczytno County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  north-east of Szczytno and  south-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
It is located in Masuria.
History
The village was founded by Polish settlers by 1414. As of 1602 the population was predominantly Polish.
